# 3point0 OS Cursor Rules

## Project
Next.js 14 app, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, dark mission control aesthetic.
Operator: Marquel Martin (non-developer). Always explain changes in plain English.

## Code rules
- Functional components only, no class components
- Always use TypeScript types
- Keep components under 150 lines — split if larger
- No inline styles — use Tailwind classes only
- Always handle loading and error states

## UI rules
- Dark theme always: background #0a0e1a, text #e2e8f0
- Primary accent: teal #00d4aa (One54), orange #f97316 (Pressbox)
- Monospace font for all labels and headers
- Subtle animations only — no heavy effects that slow the app
- Mobile-friendly but desktop-first

## Agent rules
- API keys always in .env.local, never in code
- Always check for existing data before API calls
- Show loading states during agent operations
- Log all agent actions to activity.json

## When I ask for changes
- Make the minimal change needed
- Don't refactor unrelated code
- Explain what you changed and why in 2-3 sentences
